<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,482,581]" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">
Another name which deserves attention is the combination 
<taxonomicName authority="(F. Ritter)" baseAuthorityName="F. Ritter" box="[813,1087,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eriosyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[813,975,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">Eriosyce fulva</emphasis>
(F.Ritter)
</taxonomicName>
<collectionCode box="[1095,1111,482,508]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="14" pageNumber="93" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode box="[1114,1132,482,508]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="14" pageNumber="93" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[1135,1241,482,508]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
&amp; Helmut Walter. It is invalid, because its putative basyonym (“ 
<taxonomicName authority="F. Ritter" authorityName="F. Ritter" box="[647,960,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Chileorebutia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[647,865,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">Chileorebutia fulva</emphasis>
F.Ritter
</taxonomicName>
”) is a nomen nudum (Arts. 36.1 and 37.1 of 
<collectionCode box="[136,189,554,580]" country="Colombia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xsgz-nxkh" name="Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Museo de Historia Natural" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">ICN</collectionCode>
). The valid basionym is 
<taxonomicName authority="F. Ritter" authorityName="F. Ritter" box="[462,769,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Thelocephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[462,678,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">Thelocephala fulva</emphasis>
F.Ritter
</taxonomicName>
and we here propose its combination under 
<taxonomicName box="[1265,1363,555,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eriosyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="93" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1265,1363,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="93">Eriosyce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
:
</paragraph>
